full_text: Log in as an underwriter Alice Applegate. There are several ways to search for a policy. If you know the policy number, a quick way is to click the policy drop-down menu. Type in the policy number field. Click the search icon. If the policy exists, it opens the policy file directly. The policy file is the electronic file in which Policy Center stores policy information that is part of the legal contract. The more comprehensive option is to go to the search menu at the top. Select Policies. If free text search is enabled, as in this demo, two tabs are displayed, Basic and Advanced. On the Basic page, enter the search term, for example, a partial name. Click Search. A list of policies is required. The basic search is only available when free text search has been set up. See the documentation for instructions on how to set it up. Go to the Advanced tab. This page has more criteria for searching policies and is the default option when free text search is not set up. It invokes a database search. You can select a specific transaction or just policy. To search for a company as the primary insured on the policy, enter the company name. First name and last name. Click Search. The search results are displayed. Click Reset to clear the inputs. To search for a person as the primary insured on the policy, enter first name and last name. For example, Ray Newton. If you enter first name and last name only, you must check the exact match boxes. Click Search. The search results are listed below. If exact match is not selected for names, you must enter more information. Click Search. If you search with first and last name only, but without exact match checked, an error message is displayed. Let's enter the city and state. Then try again. Click Search.  Click Search. It finds the policy successfully. Click Reset to clear the inputs. You can search by account number or policy number directly. Enter a policy number. Click Search. Click Search.  From the result list, click the policy number link to open the policy file. This is the end of demonstration for policy search.
